ely rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.504336, "shard": "02", "shelf_id": "sn84020657, 1914-02-03, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/ak", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["juneau (alaska)", "newspapers", "juneau", "alaska", "united states"], "subject_headings": ["Juneau (Alaska)--Newspapers", "Alaska--Juneau", "United States--Alaska--Juneau"], "subjects": [{"alaska": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:alaska&fo=json"}, {"juneau": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:juneau&fo=json"}, {"juneau (alaska)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:juneau+%28alaska%29&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2024-05-22T13:11:03.575Z", "title": "The Alaska daily empire (Juneau, Alaska), February 3, 1914", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84020657/1914-02-03/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84020657/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn84020657"], "batch": ["ak_albatross_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1912", "description": ["Daily (except Sunday) Vol. 1, no. 1 (Nov. 2, 1912)-v. 29, no. 4345 (Dec. 7, 1926). Also issued on microfilm from the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Daily Alaska empire 2771-2648 (DLC)sn 83045499 (OCoLC)9518436"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:11.046Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-01", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-01"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84020657/", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [58.3010372, -134.4246377], "location": ["juneau", "united states", "alaska"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-134.4246377, 58.3010372], "number": ["microfilm master", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "4340", "library of congress", "1", "2576-9227", "sn84020657", "2025-06-25t14:21:40", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84020657/1926-12-07/ed-1/", "sn83045499", "online resource", "2024-05-12t17:51:13.897021", "wisconsin hist soc, newsp proj", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84020657/1912-11-02/ed-1/", "3039521", "microfilm service copy"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["chronicling america", "catalog", "serial and government publications division", "the alaska daily empire (juneau, alaska) 1912-1926", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 40.88356, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["juneau (alaska)", "newspapers", "juneau", "alaska", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-07-22T07:34:31.418Z", "title": "The Alaska daily empire", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84020657/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218604/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1912", "dates": ["[1912 TO 1926]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sunday) Began with volume 1, no. 1 (November 2, 1912); ceased December 7, 1926. Publisher: Empire Printing Company, <Janaury 2, 1915-October 26, 1918>. Also issued on microfilm from the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Description based on: Volume 1, no. 1 (November 2, 1912); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XII, no. 1350 (OCtober 26, 1918) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 14, 2018). Daily Alaska empire 2771-2656 (DLC) 2021270909 (OCoLC)1290682950"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:41.529Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218604/", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["juneau", "united states", "alaska"], "number": ["1023038927", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2021270909", "2018218604", "2576-9235"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the alaska daily empire (juneau, alaska) 1912-1926 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 31.707945, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["juneau (alaska)", "newspapers", "juneau", "alaska", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "The Alaska daily empire", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218604/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218606/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1921", "dates": ["[1921 TO 1931]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. 23, no. 33 (July 9, 1921); ceased November 20, 1931. Description based on: Vol. 23, no. 33 (July 9, 1921); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 21, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 25 (December 30, 1922) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed February 21, 2018). Stroller's weekly"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:41.529Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218606/", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["douglas", "juneau", "united states", "alaska"], "number": ["2576-9758", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2018218606", "2018218605", "online resource", "1023801180"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the stroller's weekly and douglas island news (juneau, alaska) 1921-1931 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 31.707945, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["douglas", "juneau (alaska)", "newspapers", "douglas (juneau)", "douglas (juneau, alaska)", "juneau", "alaska", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "The Stroller's weekly and Douglas Island news", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218606/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021270909/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1926", "dates": ["[1926 TO 1964]"], "description": ["Daily (except Saturday) Began with vol. XXIX, no. 4346 (December 8, 1926); ceased July 21, 1964. Supplements accompany some numbers. J bird was issued with the Daily Alaska empire from <1932-May 16, 1936>, with separate enumeration. It then resumed publishing on its own September 25, 1936. Vol. XXIX, No. 4346 (December 8, 1926); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 3, 2022). Vol. XXX, No. 4572 (August 31, 1927) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 3, 2022). Juneau Alaska empire"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:01.956Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021270909/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["juneau", "united states", "alaska"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2771-2656", "online resource", "2021270909", "2018218604", "1290682950"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the daily alaska empire (juneau, alaska) 1926-1964 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 31.707945, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["juneau (alaska)", "newspapers", "juneau", "alaska", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:03:28.349Z", "title": "The daily Alaska empire", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021270909/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2023270612/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["alaska native brotherhood"], "date": "1923", "dates": ["[1923 TO 1932]"], "description": ["Monthly Print began with vol. 1, no. 1 (February 15, 1923); ceased in 1932? Published in Juneau, Alaska, February-April, 1923; Ketchikan, Alaska, May, 1923-<Apr. 1931>; Petersburg, Alaska <May, 1931-1932>. Issue numbering irregular. Vol. 1, No. 2 (May, 1923); title from caption (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 8, 2023). Volume 9, No. 5 (September 1932) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 8, 2023)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:09.301Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2023270612/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["petersburg", "juneau", "ketchikan", "alaska", "united states"], "number": ["2837-6269", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2023270612", "1378518132", "online resource"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the alaska fisherman (ketchikan, alaska;petersburg, alaska) 1923-1932 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["monthly"], "score": 31.707945, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["indians of north america", "juneau (alaska)", "newspapers", "petersburg", "ketchikan (alaska)", "juneau", "ketchikan", "alaska", "petersburg (alaska)", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:08:46.277Z", "title": "The Alaska fisherman", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2023270612/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2023270652/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["juneau high school (juneau, alaska)", "juneau-douglas high school (juneau, alaska)"], "date": "1923", "dates": ["[1923 TO 1999]"], "description": ["Biweekly, <1925-1936> Print began in 1923. J bird was issued with the Daily Alaska empire from <1932-May 16, 1936>, with separate enumeration. It then resumed publishing on its own September 25, 1936. Volume V, Number I (December 17, 1932); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed August 2, 2023). Vol. VIII, No. 33 (May 16, 1933) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed August 2, 2023)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:38:10.725Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2023270652/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["juneau", "united states", "alaska"], "number": ["2026-04-13t21:30:13", "online resource", "2993-7612", "2023270652", "1391997256"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Jay bird"], "partof": ["the \"j\" bird (juneau, alaska) 1923-19?? [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["biweekly"], "score": 31.707945, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["juneau high school (juneau, alaska)", "juneau (alaska)", "newspapers", "united states", "juneau-douglas high school (juneau, alaska)", "student newspapers and periodicals", "juneau", "alaska", "high schools", "high school students"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:08:46.277Z", "title": "The \"J\" bird", "type": ["title"]